addProposal((bytes32,bool,bool,uint256,u.details: Instrument instance should be created before this is called need to add authorization

beforeResolve(uint256).details: need to store internal balance that is used to calculate the redemption price

enoughLiqudity(uint256).details: for now this implies that the vault allows full utilization ratio, but the utilization ratio should be (soft)maxed and tunable by a parameter

resolveInstrument(uint256).details: In cases of default, needs to be called AFTER the principal recouperation attempts  like liquidations, auctions, etc such that the redemption price takes into account the maturity balance

addProposal((bytes32,bool,bool,uint256,u.notice: add instrument proposal created by the Utilizer

beforeResolve(uint256).notice: RESOLVE FUNCTION #1 Checks if instrument is ready to be resolved and locks capital. records blocknumber such that resolveInstrument is called after this function  records balances+PnL of instrument

denyInstrument(uint256).notice: called on market denial by controller => denied before approval

depositIntoInstrument(uint256,uint256,bo.notice: Deposit a specific amount of float into a trusted Instrument. Called when market is approved.  Also has the role of granting a credit line to a credit-based Instrument like uncol.loans

enoughLiqudity(uint256).notice: returns true if the vault has enough balance to withdraw or supply to new instrument (excluding those supplied to existing instruments)

get_vault_params().notice: called when constructed, params set by the creater of the vault

harvest(address).notice: Harvest a trusted Instrument, records profit/loss

instrumentAssetOracle(uint256,uint256,ui.notice: fetches how much asset the instrument has in underlying.

isTrusted(address).notice: returns true if Instrument is approved

mint(uint256,address).notice: a minting restrictor is set for different vaults

pingMaturity(address,bool).notice: function called when instrument resolves from within

poolZCBValue(uint256).notice: get programmatic pricing of a pool based longZCB  returns psu: price of senior(VT's share of investment) vs underlying  returns pju: price of junior(longZCB) vs underlying

pushToLM(uint256).notice: push unutilized capital to leverage vault

receiver_conditions(address).notice: types of restrictions are:  a) verified address b) reputation scores

redeem(uint256,address,address).notice: apply fee before withdrawing to prevent just minting before maturities and withdrawing after

repayDebt(address,uint256).notice: when market resolves, send back pulled collateral from managers

totalAssets().notice: Calculates the total amount of underlying tokens the Vault holds, excluding profit

trustInstrument(uint256,(uint256,uint256.notice: Stores a Instrument as trusted when its approved

trusted_transfer(uint256,address).notice: amount is always in WAD, so need to convert if decimals mismatch
